<br>
&quot;So,exactly what do you have planned for dinner?&quot; She questioned,hoping there would be human flesh somewhere in Alysia's answer.<br>
<br>
For awhile Zelia wasn't able to bring herself to kill even to eat,but lately killing didn't seem to be much of a problem. So maybe if a passing merchant or a passing anyone were to cross their path,and with all hopes attack them,Zelia just might beable to eat,and do the honors of carving the feast herself. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ualysiaofscynthia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alysia of Scynthia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 395<br> <font color=#993300>(8/27/02 2:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=377.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Feasting Upon Flesh</span><hr size=1> Alysia could only imagine what Zelia had in mind, but it was a rumor that when a Scynthian kills, they tend to feast on the flesh of their kill.<br>
