<br>
&quot;The people here have a thing against warriors. And this time around we don't want to cause a fight.&quot;<br>
<br>
But why? <br>
<br>
She began walking giving a cloak to Zelia as well. She then frowned seeing a small house with tiny children sitting outside holding onto their mother as their father was handing a tall guard a bag full of coins. <br>
<br>
&quot;Taxers.&quot; She sighed and looked to Zelia. &quot;The ruler of this village taxes the people greatly. There's no way to attack him or replace the leader as of right now without starting a war. So I try to keep the peace as much as I can.&quot;<br>
<br>
She smiled and then snuck her way over to a large boat. <br>
<br>
&quot;Come on.&quot; She looked up at the cargo on board with a grin.<br>
<br>
&quot;We have to find dinner after all.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uiizeliaii.showPublicProfile?language=EN>II Zelia II</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 164<br> <font color=#993300>(9/3/02 1:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=377.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hometown.aol.com/iizeliaii/images/zel-1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Human Flesh would be good</span><hr size=1> Zelia followed Alysias lead.<br>
